              "free_text": [
                " A slow neutron spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The silver target was a slab 4 in.x6 in. and 1.5 in.",
                "thick, having the smaller surfaces bevelled at 45",
                "degrees so as to present an area of 4 in.x4 in. to",
                "the beam with uniform slant thickness of 2.12 in. The",
                "effective target thickness in the direction of the",
                "beam was 57 g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The method consists of counting the neutrons",
                "scattered from a thick target of the element under",
                "investigation, utilizing a slow neutron spectrometer",
                "for energy determination. Although thin targets (in",
                "the sense of near unity transmission) have the",
                "advantage that the measured scattered count may be",
                "interpreted directly in terms of scattering cross",
                "section, they have the disadvantage of low counting",
                "rate and limited energy range near a resonance over",
                "which the transmission is near unity. In addition,",
                "the data generally require resolution and Doppler",
                "corrections. On the other hand, a thick target",
                "possesses none of these difficulties."
              ]
            }
          ],
